---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { pageMeta } from "../../../data/site";
import { withBase } from "../../../utils/paths";

const locale = "en";
const meta = pageMeta[locale].about;
---

<BaseLayout locale={locale} title={meta.title} description={meta.description} path={meta.path} alternatePath={meta.alternate}>
  <section class="section about-hero">
    <div class="container about-layout">
      <div class="about-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Our Story</h1>
        <p class="lead">Bloom & Fly was born from the journey of Pauline and Jean-Emmanuel, partners in life as well as in this project.</p>
        <p>Since childhood, Pauline has been particularly sensitive to stress, a presence that grew stronger over the years. Then a health issue changed everything. This experience brought her back to what truly matters: listening to her body, slowing down, and seeking what truly helps her feel better. She explored many different practices, each one helping her better understand her own needs.</p>
        <p>Jean-Emmanuel, on the other hand, is her exact opposite, rarely stressed, yet affected by other imbalances: fragile sleep, difficulty focusing, and a mind that tends to scatter.</p>
        <p>Two different personalities, two different ways of living everyday life... and yet, the same need: simple practices to refocus, calm down, and regain balance.</p>
        <p>It is from this complementarity that Bloom & Fly was created: an app designed to support everyone according to their needs, whether they are seeking calm, energy, or greater inner harmony. A soothing and caring space where everyone can explore, at their own pace, what truly makes them feel good, even in just a few minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <img src={withBase("/assets/brand/logo-pastille.png")} alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="narrow text-section">
      <h2>Our mission</h2>
      <p>Our mission is to support everyone in achieving real and lasting well-being by offering a simple and structured space to restore calm, stability, and energy in everyday life.</p>
      <p>In a context where the pace of life is accelerating and stress is becoming omnipresent, Bloom & Fly helps everyone, regardless of age or level of experience, reintroduce well-being into their day, even when time is limited.</p>
      <p>Our ambition is to make well-being practical and accessible, so that everyone can reconnect with what makes them feel good and build a more balanced routine, day after day.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft values-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Values</p>
      <h2>Our values</h2>
      <p class="lead">Our values are at the heart of Bloom & Fly. They guide each of our practices and everything we share with you.</p>
      <div class="values-grid">
        <article class="card value-card">
          <h3>Listening</h3>
          <p>Bloom & Fly places listening at the center of its approach. We encourage everyone to reconnect with their feelings, their needs, and their own pace.</p>
          <p>This value also guides the relationship we aim to build with our community: being attentive to their feedback so we can help Bloom & Fly evolve in a way that is fair, useful, and aligned with the real needs of our future users.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card value-card">
          <h3>Kindness</h3>
          <p>We support each person with respect, gentleness, and without pressure. Everyone moves at their own pace, according to what they feel in the moment. Our intention is to offer a welcoming, soothing space where it’s possible to pause, breathe, and take care of yourself without judgment.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card value-card">
          <h3>Fulfillment</h3>
          <p>Bloom & Fly is a space designed to support inner growth.</p>
          <p>We encourage exploration, self-discovery, and the integration of practices that support lasting balance, so everyone can discover themselves, evolve, and grow at their own pace.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(120deg, rgba(223, 242, 251, 0.85), rgba(255, 241, 235, 0.8));
  }

  .about-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(12rem, 18rem);
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-layout img {
    justify-self: center;
    width: min(18rem, 70vw);
    height: auto;
  }

  .about-copy p:not(.eyebrow),
  .text-section p {
    font-size: clamp(1.08rem, 1.3vw, 1.16rem);
    line-height: 1.78;
  }

  .about-copy p:last-child,
  .text-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .values-section .lead {
    margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.1rem;
    counter-reset: values;
  }

  .value-card {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 17rem;
    padding: 1.55rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    background:
      linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9), rgba(223, 242, 251, 0.38)),
      rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
  }

  .value-card:nth-child(1) {
    grid-column: span 5;
  }

  .value-card:nth-child(2) {
    grid-column: span 7;
  }

  .value-card:nth-child(3) {
    grid-column: 3 / span 8;
  }

  .value-card::before {
    counter-increment: values;
    content: counter(values, decimal-leading-zero);
    display: inline-grid;
    place-items: center;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--dream), var(--aqua));
    color: white;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 2.4vw, 2.05rem);
  }

  .value-card p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .value-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .value-card:nth-child(1),
    .value-card:nth-child(2),
    .value-card:nth-child(3) {
      grid-column: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
